<h2 id="theorem-on-parity">Theorem on Parity</h2>
<p>Permutations can also be described in terms of their parity. Any
length n cycle of a permutation can be expressed as the product of
2-cycles.</p>
<p>The cube always has even parity, or an even number of cubies
exchanged from the starting position.</p>
