<h2 id="bottom-up-algorithm">Bottom Up Algorithm</h2>
<p>A general and quite commonly used Rubik’s Cube Solution is solving a
cube layer by layer:</p>
<ul>
<li>Pick a face</li>
<li>solve for the edges</li>
<li>then solve corners</li>
<li>Go down to the next layer solve for the edges (sisnce there are no
corners)</li>
<li>Go to the final layer, solve for the edge and solve corners</li>
</ul>
